For today’s drills you’ll need a block. If you do not have a block you can use a thick book. Please keep in mind that achieving the splits is not an overnight journey and does take time. Try not to feel discouraged or frustrated and enjoy each moment of your growth. It took me about two months of consistency to achieve my full split but even then all practices are different! Practices makes progress 💙🙏🏽
—
Sorry for the delay! I think this is the universe telling me I need to take this party over to YouTube for longer videos and less hassle 😆
—
Thanks for joining me for this series! Keep up with your practice and let me see those splits 😝!

How often should you practice? Depends on your goals. Are you longing for a specific pose? Then you gotta put in the work. Ideally I suggest practicing 5-6 times a week. At minimum, 30 mins practice.
—
Personally, I practice every day for at least an hour. My practice consists of asana, meditation and breath work(pranayama).
—
Where do you start?
Sun Salutations, A, B and C.  From there begin to add on other drills that align with what you want out of your practice 💕

node.text:
Root to Grow 🌱
—
In each posture (asana) find the stability and steadiness (sthira) from your root through engagement of the core and other muscles and a strong foundation guided by intention in your movements.  To this, add mobility and ease (sukha) through mindful and focused breath and softness of the face and mind. You set the pace and tempo of your practice with the breath you draw in and release.
—
Breath is important for flexibility. When you’re breathing not only are you drawing in energy (prana) for the muscles but you are providing your mind with something to focus on. Get rid of the outside thoughts and visualize each inhale and exhale 💙

node.text:
How long does it take to achieve the splits? There is no set time frame as every BODY is different but with the right amount of work, consistency and breath you will definitely see progress in your range of motion within a few weeks. Practice makes progress.
—
When I first started practicing yoga I could barely touch my toes, my body and breath connection was super off and I pretty much had no spatial awareness. Every time I moved, my mind would tell me I looked weird or silly. Mentally, I was filled with self hate. Yoga helped me tune in with MY body and understand the way it moves. Take your time to listen to your body, step out of your mind and let your body flow to the connection of your breath. Once your mind can appreciate that connection without judgment or comparison then invite it in for the ultimate union of mind, breath and body. For me, that is yoga 💙

—
If you have any questions email me or shoot me a DM ✨

Today is the day! Last episode of season 1 of @comeinpeacepodcast airs tonight @ 8pm EST on our YouTube channel 🥰💜✌🏽
—
I just wanna say thank you to my beautiful cast members @abby.1908 @justkeeya and @boxer_knockout for joining me along this ride of being raw, real and candid as we talk about all the tings. Thank you to @yopointofview0455 and @drewharmony for seeing the vision and putting up with me 😆 and also thank you @rmkwrld for taking the best photos. Thank you to the production team and thank you to @fusionsuperplex for believing in us and holding space for our platform andddd for all the amazing food, drinks and vibes 💜🙏🏽
—
Last but not least, thank you to everyone who has supported, subscribed, shared and all that good stuff 💜 we all appreciate you. See y’all for season two ✌🏽✌🏽🤩💜💜💜💜
